------<br>
<br>
Yes but it is not always *you* . Us &quot;overpowered&quot; skalds are rarely the first targets. Our enemies tries to disable healers/runies/spiritmasters first, they are the prime targets, not us. A typical melee class attacks more than he is hit imho.<br>
<br>
However, this is not the real problem with defensive skills in RvR.<br>
<br>
Parry only work on frontal attacks. In your standard confused RvR melee (not in duels of course), attacks come from the flanks and the rear as often as from the front.<br>
<br>
So, yes, you have less opportunities to parry than to attack in RvR <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c2a2><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showUserPublicProfile?gid=mbolme>mbolme</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Participant</span><br>  Posts: 23<br> <font color=#ff0000>(10/24/02 7:32 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=366.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Skald Realm Abilities</span><hr size=1> &gt; Yes but it is not always *you* . Us &quot;overpowered&quot; skalds are rarely the first targets. Our <br>
